news.title: Karnataka: Property registration, April-May revenues hit a new high
news.para: The state has witnessed 1.8 lakh property registrations in April and 1.96 lakh in May, according to the department of stamps and registration.

news.title: Gurugram deputy commissioner orders probe after AVL 36A buyers' allegations
news.para: Deputy commissioner formed a committee comprising sub-divisional-magistrate (SDM) and district town planner (DTP) to investigate the allegations and also check if there is any violation of provision of Affordable Housing policy in AVL36A.

news.title: Working on TDR norms, will be ready by mid-June: Goa TCP minister
news.para: The TCP board met on Thursday and deliberated on the criteria for zones where the TDR could be applied and utilised. Rane said that while concerns about the application of the TDR remain, the TCP board is in favour of the policy.

news.title: DTCP to finalise firms for Chintels Paradiso testing in a week
news.para: According to senior DTCP officials, these agencies will work in coordination with IIT-Delhi and submit their reports to the special investigation team (SIT) probing the collapse, based on which the future course of action will be decided.

news.title: DLF plans to invest Rs 3,000 crore over six years in retail push
news.para: The company has planned malls in Gurugram and Goa and high streets in Gurugram, in addition to retail space in its upcoming residential and commercial developments, the majority of which will be launched this year.

news.title: ADIA to buy 20% stake in IIFL Home Finance for Rs 2,200 crore
news.para: ​IIFL Home Finance, a wholly owned subsidiary of IIFL Finance, proposes to use the additional capital to continue its expansion into new markets to meet growing demand for housing loans.

news.title: Commonwealth Bank of Australia leases around 1,35,000 sq ft office space in Bengaluru
news.para: “There are growing numbers of managed office deal that were recently signed. The recently deal with CBA only reaffirms it and has 48 months commitment,” said a person aware of the deal.

news.title: Centre to form state committees for better execution of RERA orders
news.para: A senior official from the ministry of housing and urban affairs told TOI on Thursday that a detailed note on the Centre's recent decision on the formation of the committees had been sent to all states.

news.title: UK annual house prices slow for third month in a row: Halifax
news.para: Prices rose by 10.5% compared with May last year, down from April's 10.8% increase to show the smallest increase since January.

news.title: Special PMLA court directs CBI to restore DHFL promoter's custody to Taloja prison
news.para: Wadhwan’s lawyers had approached the court contending that the transfer to UP was “ prima facie not as per law” as they were taken from Taloja jail without the court’s permission or knowledge.

news.title: Turkey set to cap rent increases at 25% as inflation soars
news.para: Annual inflation hit its highest since 1998 at 73.5% last month due to soaring energy prices and an easing cycle by the central bank in accordance with President Tayyip Erdogan's economic plan that prioritises production, exports, growth and low rates.

news.title: Ludhiana: Draw of lots for Atal apartments on June 16
news.para: Land acquisition collector (LAC) Neetu Katyal on Thursday reviewed the final arrangements for this mega event scheduled to be held on June 16 at Nehru Siddhant Kendra.

news.title: Polycab India promoter buys duplex in Mumbai's Prabhadevi for Rs 48 crore
news.para: In November, Hindalco Industries, part of the Aditya Birla Group, had acquired a 100% equity stake in Polycab India’s wholly-owned subsidiary Ryker Base Private Ltd for an enterprise value of Rs 323 crore.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat committed to invest Rs 9,000-crore to expand its manufacturing capacity
news.para: Dalmia Bharat has a Cement production capacity of 35.9 MTPA (million tonnes per annum) and aims to achieve a production capacity of 48.5 MTPA in FY24. Over the next decade, it expects to expand capacity to about 110-130 MTPA.

news.title: Bombay HC asks ED not to take possession of assets of ARA properties
news.para: The adjudicating authority (AA) under the Prevention of Money Laundering Act (PMLA) had recently confirmed the provisional attachments of assets of ARA properties.
